    "revise": "You are the FIGURE REVISER (Opus) for \"The LLM Stack\". Chapter: content/10-multimodal-and-arch/05-unified-any-to-any.md\nThe chapter's core intuitions: Tokenize-everything: if every modality can be expressed as a sequence of integers from a codebook, the ordinary autoregressive next-token objective already knows how to model it \u2014 no task-specific heads required.; VQ-VAE turns a continuous image into discrete tokens by snapping each encoder feature-map cell to its nearest codebook vector, then flattening the grid into a 1-D integer sequence the same length as a paragraph.; The quantisation gap: a codebook index carries ~13 bits per cell while a raw pixel patch carries ~24 bits, so discrete tokenisation throws information away \u2014 this is the ceiling Transfusion tries to escape.; Chameleon = pure early fusion: one shared embedding table over a joint 65K vocab, a uniform causal mask over interleaved text+image tokens, and a single cross-entropy loss.\n\nReview each of these figures (the ones this chapter just drew/edited):\n  ar-vs-diffusion-image-generation\n\nFor EACH: render and SEE it \u2014 `python3 scripts/preview_fig.py <NAME> --theme both` from /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook,\nthen view /tmp/figpreview/<NAME>.light.png and .dark.png. Judge strictly:\n  - Does it actually BUILD INTUITION for its concept (not just decorate)? Is it correct vs the chapter?\n  - Theme-safe (no hardcoded primary color; readable in BOTH light and dark)?\n  - Nothing clipped by the viewBox; no illegible overlaps; no tofu glyphs (ASCII only in the SVG)?\n  - Marker present in the chapter exactly once; figcaption has a bold lead + takeaway?\nIf a figure has ANY problem, FIX it: Edit /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook/figures/<NAME>.html (and re-render to confirm), or\nfix a missing/duplicate marker in the chapter. Re-verify after fixing.\n\nSet verdict per figure: good / fixed / still-broken / missing. `passed` = every figure good-or-fixed\nAND present. Return the structured object."
