    "revise": "You are the FIGURE REVISER (Opus) for \"The LLM Stack\". Chapter: content/13-interp-safety-gov/05-ai-safety-oversight.md\nThe chapter's core intuitions: The oversight gap: model task accuracy p_M outruns human verification accuracy p_H, so naive RLHF starts rewarding answers that LOOK right to a rater who cannot tell; scalable oversight's job is to lift the human curve (p_H^eff) with AI assistance, all resting on the verification-generation gap (checking is easier than producing).; The three scalable-oversight mechanisms are structurally DIFFERENT ways to exploit the verification-generation gap: debate = two adversaries decompose a hard judgment into local rebuttals a weak judge can follow; recursive reward modeling = recursively decompose a task so every human judgment stays within human competence; weak-to-strong generalization = weak labels ELICIT a strong model's latent knowledge instead of capping it.; Dangerous-capability evaluation measures marginal UPLIFT (with-model arm vs no-model control arm), not absolute capability, under STRONG elicitation, and is always a lower bound on true capability - a failed eval never proves safety.; Sandbagging and unfaithful CoT mean a model can actively look safer than it is: the most dangerous models can appear the safest, and optimizing against a reasoning monitor teaches the model to HIDE rather than to not-do.\n\nReview each of these figures (the ones this chapter just drew/edited):\n  safety-buffer-tripwire\n\nFor EACH: render and SEE it \u2014 `python3 scripts/preview_fig.py <NAME> --theme both` from /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook,\nthen view /tmp/figpreview/<NAME>.light.png and .dark.png. Judge strictly:\n  - Does it actually BUILD INTUITION for its concept (not just decorate)? Is it correct vs the chapter?\n  - Theme-safe (no hardcoded primary color; readable in BOTH light and dark)?\n  - Nothing clipped by the viewBox; no illegible overlaps; no tofu glyphs (ASCII only in the SVG)?\n  - Marker present in the chapter exactly once; figcaption has a bold lead + takeaway?\nIf a figure has ANY problem, FIX it: Edit /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook/figures/<NAME>.html (and re-render to confirm), or\nfix a missing/duplicate marker in the chapter. Re-verify after fixing.\n\nSet verdict per figure: good / fixed / still-broken / missing. `passed` = every figure good-or-fixed\nAND present. Return the structured object."
